      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Messy trees, especially with multiple PPs, are a classic sign that you need to properly categorize the function of the phrase, like having one as an Adjunct and another as a Complement. If you have several PPs piling up, they usually attach higher up, often directly to the VP, sticking out like a cluster of scrawny, co-dependent little green goblins. The key to keeping it clean is realizing that adjuncts (extra details) often branch off the main VP node before subsequent modifiers are attached.",
      "source": "target",
